"I'm tired and I want to go to bed

970
01:58:04,876 --> 01:58:08,088
"I had a little drink about a hour ago

971
01:58:08,213 --> 01:58:11,299
"And it's gone right to my head

972
01:58:11,383 --> 01:58:14,260
"Wherever I may roam

973
01:58:14,803 --> 01:58:17,639
"On land or sea or foam

974
01:58:17,806 --> 01:58:21,976
"You can always hear me singing this..."

975
01:58:25,980 --> 01:58:27,899
Start the engines.

976
01:58:40,453 --> 01:58:41,913
Fire her up!

977
01:58:52,799 --> 01:58:55,010
Put out the fire, will ya?

978
01:59:07,147 --> 01:59:09,190
- Pump her out.
- Done.

979
01:59:20,160 --> 01:59:23,121
- Everybody on deck.
- He ate the light.

980
01:59:23,246 --> 01:59:25,206
- Terrific.
- Excuse me.

981
01:59:28,418 --> 01:59:32,088
Quint, what are you doing?
Don't waste your time.

982
01:59:34,049 --> 01:59:36,176
What's wrong with this?

983
01:59:39,137 --> 01:59:43,933
Hooper, take the wheel.
Brody, follow that. Watch for him.

984
02:00:06,081 --> 02:00:07,749
You okay?

985
02:00:10,377 --> 02:00:11,670
You okay?

986
02:00:43,326 --> 02:00:45,078
More left rudder.

987
02:00:46,204 --> 02:00:48,039
Pull your left hand down.

988
02:00:48,164 --> 02:00:51,793
I can't. It'll only go about three inches.

989
02:00:51,960 --> 02:00:56,715
All of our injectors got scored
from the salt water in the fuel.

990
02:00:58,091 --> 02:01:01,302
Yeah, the housing's bent, you can hear it.

991
02:01:02,345 --> 02:01:07,934
Try the left rudder again. More left.
Good. Once again now.

992
02:01:13,023 --> 02:01:14,524
There it is.

993
02:01:14,983 --> 02:01:17,110
What do you say, Chief?

994
02:01:17,360 --> 02:01:20,572
The barrel is up, it's right in the stern.

995
02:01:25,326 --> 02:01:29,622
I think he's right under the keg.
Grab the boat hook.

996
02:01:45,096 --> 02:01:47,599
If we can get close enough...

997
02:01:48,850 --> 02:01:54,731
...l've got things on board that'll kill it.
- Just want to goose him up. Come on.

998
02:02:09,496 --> 02:02:13,792
When he runs, you drop that rope
or you'll lose your hands.

999
02:02:15,919 --> 02:02:21,216
I've seen fingers torn out at the knuckles.
Whole sea's bones, full of 'em.

1000
02:02:21,758 --> 02:02:23,885
Give it to me a minute.

1001
02:02:43,113 --> 02:02:46,241
Haul in that line or it'll foul us.

1002
02:02:47,325 --> 02:02:49,160
Start the engine.

1003
02:02:51,663 --> 02:02:55,667
- Where are you goin'?
- I'm gonna make a phone call.

1004
02:03:04,092 --> 02:03:07,137
Hello, mayday, Orca. Coast Guard?

1005
02:03:08,722 --> 02:03:11,599
Coast Guard, this is the Orca.
Do you read me?

1006
02:03:11,683 --> 02:03:14,811
Coast Guard, this is the Orca. Do you...

1007
02:03:22,444 --> 02:03:24,362
Excuse me, Chief.

1008
02:03:25,113 --> 02:03:30,785
That's great. That's just great.
Now, where the hell are we?

1009
02:03:33,371 --> 02:03:38,126
You're certifiable, Quint.
You know that? You're certifiable.

1010
02:03:38,293 --> 02:03:42,172
- You're certifiable, but I'll tell you this!
- Boys.

1011
02:03:44,507 --> 02:03:48,011
I think he's come back for his noon feeding.

1012
02:03:49,512 --> 02:03:51,681
Hook me up another barrel.

1013
02:04:30,053 --> 02:04:32,347
Bring her around after him.

1014
02:04:53,410 --> 02:04:56,413
Full throttle.
Get me right up alongside of him.

1015
02:04:56,538 --> 02:05:00,625
I can't rev it up that high,
it's not gonna take it.

1016
02:05:23,064 --> 02:05:25,066
Five degrees port.

1017
02:05:33,825 --> 02:05:36,202
All right, hold your course.

1018
02:05:43,960 --> 02:05:46,421
Five degrees port now.

1019
02:05:50,800 --> 02:05:52,594
Hold your course.

1020
02:05:54,888 --> 02:05:57,182
- Fast fish.
- Watch my hand.

1021
02:05:59,100 --> 02:06:03,355
Be sure you watch my hand.
Follow me. Follow me.

1022
02:06:05,106 --> 02:06:08,568
Lad, you watch him now.
Starboard. Starboard.

1023
02:06:10,070 --> 02:06:11,613
Run him down.

1024
02:06:21,414 --> 02:06:23,083
Hard apart.

1025
02:06:27,587 --> 02:06:28,797
Watch him.

1026
02:06:28,922 --> 02:06:30,382
Starboard.

1027
02:07:00,954 --> 02:07:05,083
I can't believe it.
Two barrels and he's going down again.

1028
02:07:11,923 --> 02:07:13,717
It's incredible.

1029
02:07:21,516 --> 02:07:23,893
- They're up again!
- Now what?

1030
02:07:35,238 --> 02:07:40,535
Why don't we lead the shark into shore
instead of him leading us out to sea?

1031
02:07:46,291 --> 02:07:48,418
Grab a couple of poles.

1032
02:07:51,296 --> 02:07:53,965
Hang on now, we're going around.

1033
02:07:54,799 --> 02:07:57,886
Into starboard. Easy.

1034
02:07:59,095 --> 02:08:03,641
I'm gonna back her off now.
Keep a watch on it, boys. Watch him.

1035
02:08:09,898 --> 02:08:12,442
All right, gentlemen, snag them.

1036
02:08:19,324 --> 02:08:22,535
Now then tie them to the stern cleats.

1037
02:08:26,289 --> 02:08:29,542
Brody, bring your end around the cleat.

1038
02:08:30,502 --> 02:08:34,798
That's right, it'll lock itself off.
Give him room, Brody.

1039
02:08:37,175 --> 02:08:39,302
Stay clear of the line.

1040
02:08:49,479 --> 02:08:51,606
Watch it. Stand clear.

1041
02:09:04,202 --> 02:09:07,539
Stand away from those stern cleats.

1042
02:09:23,847 --> 02:09:26,307
Back home we got a taxidermy man.

1043
02:09:26,433 --> 02:09:30,603
He gonna have a heart attack
when he sees what I brought him.

1044
02:09:39,320 --> 02:09:43,158
Throttle back. You're losing the cleats.

1045
02:09:45,910 --> 02:09:49,247
My God, this one, too. They're both going.

1046
02:09:49,664 --> 02:09:55,045
- He's eating his way through that line.
- He's working his way right up to us.

1047
02:09:55,837 --> 02:09:58,923
Come on, Quint. Hurry!

1048
02:10:01,384 --> 02:10:02,927
Out of my way.

1049
02:10:09,517 --> 02:10:10,810
Watch it.

1050
02:10:15,857 --> 02:10:19,069
Untie this. He'll pull out the transom.

1051
02:10:23,907 --> 02:10:25,575
Make it fast.

1052
02:10:26,826 --> 02:10:29,245
I can't. It's trying to run.

1053
02:10:32,916 --> 02:10:35,377
Pull, you son of a bitch!

1054
02:10:38,546 --> 02:10:41,508
Go ahead. Pull your bloody heart out.

1055
02:10:49,974 --> 02:10:51,726
It's impossible!

1056
02:11:12,372 --> 02:11:14,916
We're breaking up! Cut it!

1057
02:11:16,751 --> 02:11:18,545
Watch your hands!

1058
02:11:19,796 --> 02:11:22,382
Cut it quick. I can't hold it!

1059
02:11:49,034 --> 02:11:52,037
He can't stay down
with three barrels on him.

1060
02:11:52,162 --> 02:11:54,873
Not with three barrels, he can't.

1061
02:11:55,206 --> 02:11:57,042
What about us?

1062
02:11:59,085 --> 02:12:02,756
Get the pump out of the locker
in front of you, will you?

1063
02:12:02,839 --> 02:12:04,758
We're gonna sink, aren't we?

1064
02:12:04,883 --> 02:12:08,303
Keep an eye on the barrels.
Pump it out, Chief.

1065
02:12:16,686 --> 02:12:18,605
Starting to go under.

1066
02:12:19,397 --> 02:12:23,193
He can't with three barrels on him.
Not with three he can't.

1067
02:13:06,736 --> 02:13:09,406
You ever have one do this before?

1068
02:13:12,409 --> 02:13:13,702
No.

1069
02:13:53,158 --> 02:13:55,910
He's chasin' us. I don't believe it.

1070
02:14:03,376 --> 02:14:06,129
I'm gonna draw him into the shallows.

1071
02:14:06,254 --> 02:14:11,134
Draw him into the shallow water.
I'm gonna draw him in and drown him.

1072
02:14:11,676 --> 02:14:14,679
- We're headin' in, Brody.
- Thank Christ!

1073
02:14:24,439 --> 02:14:27,567
- You ever had a great white do that?
- No.

1074
02:14:35,450 --> 02:14:37,619
How far do we have to go?

1075
02:14:41,247 --> 02:14:44,459
Don't put that much pressure on it.

1076
02:14:56,971 --> 02:15:00,558
- Goddamn it.
- Shut up. Get back there.

1077
02:15:07,732 --> 02:15:08,983
Hold on.

1078
02:15:28,003 --> 02:15:33,675
"Farewell and adieu to you,
fair Spanish ladies

1079
02:15:37,345 --> 02:15:43,435
"Farewell and adieu, you ladies of Spain

1080
02:15:45,353 --> 02:15:50,483
"For we received order
for to sail back to Boston"

1081
02:15:52,318 --> 02:15:55,321
You idiot, you burned out the bearings.

1082
02:15:57,407 --> 02:16:01,661
All right stop the boat. Stop the boat.
Stop it.

1083
02:18:06,411 --> 02:18:10,123
What exactly can you do
with these things of yours?

1084
02:18:15,420 --> 02:18:20,508
I think I can pump 20 ccm
of strychnine nitrate into him.

1085
02:18:21,092 --> 02:18:23,345
If I can get close enough.

1086
02:18:26,973 --> 02:18:30,101
Get this little needle through his skin?

1087
02:18:32,520 --> 02:18:34,481
No, I can't do that.

1088
02:18:36,274 --> 02:18:40,153
If I can get him close to the cage,
I can get him in the mouth.

1089
02:18:40,278 --> 02:18:45,116
- That shark'll rip that cage to pieces.
- You got any better suggestions?

1090
02:19:17,565 --> 02:19:18,858
Easy.

1091
